01/09/2006
BUCHAREST, Romania -- President Traian Basescu met with Danish Prime Minister Anders Fogh Rasmussen on Thursday (31 August) regarding Romania's scheduled EU accession on 1 January.
They also discussed developments in Lebanon and Romania's deployments in Iraq and Afghanistan.
From Bucharest, Rasmussen flew to Sofia for talks with Bulgarian counterpart Sergey Stanishev.
Rasmussen praised progress made towards the country's scheduled EU accession in January, but reiterated that EU member countries expect the government to continue addressing problems with the judicial system.
(Sega - 01/09/06;
Mediapool, News.bg, Focus, Rompres - 31/08/06)
